The governor of Ebonyi State, David Umahi, yesterday suspended  all forms of payment of income tax and hawker’s permit by traders in the state. Governor Umahi also banned all form of activities of agents of revenue collectors, including those employed by local government councils. He announced this at a town hall meeting held at Pa Ngele Oruta stadium where he addressed issues of internally generated revenue (IGR) in the state, He expressed dismay that about N1.2 billion got lost monthly to illegal revenue collectors in the state. The governor declared: “Collection of revenue from all the 13 local government areas is hereby suspended, our people should not be harassed henceforth, and anybody who disobeys will serve five months imprisonment. “So, new collection would be based on what the state agrees and it would be determined at the state executive council on Thursday and Friday.”